1 6. "Excavation" means the act or operation of excavating;
2 7. "Excavator" means a person or public agency that intends to
3 excavate or demolish within this state;
4 8. "Notification center" means the statewide center currently
5 known as the Oklahoma One-Call System, Inc., which has as one of its
6 purposes to receive notification of planned excavation and
7 demolition in a specified area from excavators, and to disseminate
8 such notification of planned excavation or demolition to operators
9 who are members and participants;
10 9. "Operator" shall mean and include any person or public
11 agency owning or operating underground facilities;
12 10. "Permitted project" means a project where a permit for the
13 work to be performed must be issued by a state or federal agency
14 and, as a prerequisite to receiving such permit, the applicant must
15 locate all underground facilities in the area of the work and in the
16 vicinity of any blasting and notify each owner of such underground
17 facilities;
18 11. "Person" includes any individual, partnership, corporation,
19 association, cooperative, trust or other entity, including a person
20 engaged as a contractor by a public agency, but not including a
21 public agency;
22 12. "Preengineered project" means a public project wherein the
23 public agency responsible for such project, as part of its
24 engineering and contract procedures, holds a meeting prior to the
ENGR. H. B. NO. 1666 Page 4

1 comm encement of any construction work on such project in which all
2 persons, determined by the public agency, in consultation with the
3 statewide one-call notification center, to have underground
4 facilities located within the construction area of the project are
5 invited to attend and given an opportunity to verify or inform the
6 public agency of the location of their underground facilities, if
7 any, within the construction area and where the location of all
8 known underground facilities are duly located or noted on the
9 engineering drawing and specifications for the project;
10 13. "Public agency" means the state, or any board, commission,
11 or agency of the state;
12 14. "Routine maintenance" means the grading of roads and barrow
13 or drainage ditches, the removal and replacement of pavement,
14 including excavation relating thereto and the installation and
15 maintenance of drainage and bridge facilities, signs, guardrails,
16 and electrical and communications facilities in or on the public
17 rights-of-way by a public agency;
18 15. "Underground facility" means any underground line, cable,
19 facility, system and appurtenances thereto, for producing, storing,
20 conveying, transmitting or distributing communication (including
21 voice, video, or data information), electricity, power, light, heat,
22 intrastate and interstate gas pipelines, as described in 49 CFR Part
23 192.1, intrastate and interstate hazardous liquid or carbon dioxide
24 pipelines, as described in 49 CFR Part 195.1, water (including storm
ENGR. H. B. NO. 1666 Page 5

1 wate r), steam, sewage and other commodities and any oil and gas
2 pipeline located in a private or public easement or right-of-way;
3 16. "Design" or "survey" means a notice to facility operators
4 to provide underground facility information during the design or
5 engineering phase of a project to mitigate potential impact to
6 existing underground facilities;
7 17. "Watch and protect" means an operator or its designated
8 representative is present to observe an excavation within ten (10)
9 feet of the operator's marking of its existing underground facility;
10 18. "Pre-excavation meeting request" means a notice to
11 underground facility operators to participate in scheduled meetings
12 for the purpose of planning large projects and coordinate resources
13 accordingly; and
14 19. "Large projects" are those excavation projects that involve
15 one of the following:
16 a. exceeds distances defined in paragraph 5 of subsection
17 D of Section 142.6 of this title, or
18 b. estimated duration is more than ninety (90) days.
19 SECTION 2. This act shall become effective November 1, 2025.
